options.text: You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet
LA Tech Week Kickoff: A Triple Header Day of Womens Empowerment Movies on the Big Screen
Presented with the City of West Hollywood
Join us for an unforgettable day celebrating the power of womens stories, voices, and impact. In partnership with the City of West Hollywood, were kicking off
with a cinematic triple feature that inspires, educates, and empowers.
All Day PASS available NOW - Your All day pass includes all three films, free signed Show Her the Money book, networking breakfast and lunch, plus the after panels and awards!
Individual Movie tickets will be available Sept 13th.
This event is sponsored by the Sunset Marquis and Holland &  Knight.
The first purchased 100 VIP tickets will receive a complementary copy of the beautiful #1 best-seller Show Her the Money coffee table book ($50 Value)
Pick your book up the morning of the event.
Book signing 9-10am with the movies Executive Producers
: Emmy award winning actress Sharon Gless (Cagney & Lacey), Catherine Gray, Dawn Lafreeda and Diana Greshtchuk.

Shining a light on the fact that women receive less than 2% of venture capital funding, this award-winning documentary demystifies the VC world and showcases visionary female founders. Special in-person appearance by
Executive Producer & Cast Member, Emmy Award-winning actress Sharon Gless
). Plus Award for actress Sharon Gless.
, whose fight for equal pay led to the historic Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act, signed into law by President Obama. Featuring Academy Award-nominated actress
A behind-the-scenes look at the making of the beloved classic
and the ongoing fight for workplace equality, featuring icons
Lily Tomlin, Jane Fonda, and Dolly Parton
These stories span business, politics, and pop culturereminding us that real change is made when womens voices are amplified.
- Coffee and Bagels in the Lobby & Book signing With Actress/Producer Sharon Gless, Director Ky Dickens, Producers Catherine Gray, Dawn Lafreeda and Diana Greshtchuk, all featured in the book!
- SHOW HER THE MONEY and After Panel with Cast and Producers
- Casual Lunch and Mixer in the Lobby
- STILL WORKING 9 to 5 and After Panel
625 N San Vicente Blvd, West Hollywood, CA 90069, USA
